Introduction
Welcome to the Sample API documentation. This API allows you to retrieve, create, update, and delete resources.
Base URL: https://api.example.com/v1
Authentication
This API uses Bearer Token Authentication. Include the token in the Authorization header:
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
Endpoints
1. Get All Items
Request:
GET /items
Host: api.example.com
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
Response:
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Sample Item",
    "price": 9.99
  }
]
2. Get a Single Item
Request:
GET /items/{id}
Host: api.example.com
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
Response:
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Sample Item",
  "price": 9.99
}
3. Create an Item
Request:
POST /items
Host: api.example.com
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New Item",
  "price": 19.99
}
Response:
{
  "id": 2,
  "name": "New Item",
  "price": 19.99
}
4. Update an Item
Request:
PUT /items/{id}
Host: api.example.com
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Item",
  "price": 14.99
}
Response:
{
  "id": 2,
  "name": "Updated Item",
  "price": 14.99
}
5. Delete an Item
Request:
DELETE /items/{id}
Host: api.example.com
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
Response:
{
  "message": "Item deleted successfully"
}
Error Responses
Standard error responses follow this format:
{
  "error": "Invalid request",
  "message": "Detailed error description"
}
| Status Code | Description            |
|-------------|------------------------|
| 200         | Success                |
| 201         | Created                |
| 400         | Bad Request            |
| 401         | Unauthorized           |
| 404         | Nor Found              |
| 500         | Internal Server Error  |
